| 2017 || January 30 || Government investigation || The Culture, Media and Sports Committee of the United Kingdom Parliament launches an investigation into "fake news".<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.wired.co.uk/article/uk-fake-news-inquiry|title = UK launches inquiry into the 'phenomenon of fake news'. MPs will investigate where fake news comes from, how it spreads and what its impact is|date = January 30, 2017|accessdate = May 22, 2017|publisher = ''Wired''}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.parliament.uk/business/committees/committees-a-z/commons-select/culture-media-and-sport-committee/news-parliament-2015/fake-news-launch-16-17/|title = 'Fake news' inquiry launched|publisher = United Kingdom Parliament|date = January 30, 2017|accessdate = May 22, 2017}}</ref> The Committee would conclude its work by May 3, 2017, at which point it would cease to exist due to the dissolution of Parliament.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.parliament.uk/business/committees/committees-a-z/commons-select/culture-media-and-sport-committee/inquiries/parliament-2015/inquiry2/|title = 'Fake news' inquiry|publisher = United Kingdom Parliament|accessdate = May 22, 2017}}</ref> || United Kingdom
